        "text": "Here are some of the best cities for digital nomads in 2024, known for their affordability, quality of life, coworking spaces, and visa options:  \n\n---\n\n### **1. Lisbon, Portugal**  \n- **Why?** Great weather, affordable cost of living, strong digital nomad community.  \n- **Visa:** [Portugal Digital Nomad Visa (D7)](https://www.portugal.com/guides/digital-nomad-visa)  \n- **Coworking spaces:** [Second Home Lisboa](https://secondhome.io/lisbon), [Outsite Lisbon](https://www.outsite.co/lisbon)  \n- **Nomad resources:** [Nomad List - Lisbon](https://nomadlist.com/lisbon-portugal)  \n\n---\n\n### **2. Chiang Mai, Thailand**  \n- **Why?** Cheap living, vibrant expat scene, excellent food, easy visa runs.  \n- **Visa:** [Thailand Elite Visa](https://thailand-elite.com/) or [Tourist Visa](https://www.thaiembassy.com/)  \n- **Coworking spaces:** [Punspace](https://punspace.com/), [CAMP](https://cmc.co.th/camp/)  \n- **Nomad resources:** [Chiang Mai Digital Nomad Guide](https://www.travelfish.org/beginners_detail/thailand/1)  \n\n---\n\n### **3. Medellín, Colombia**  \n- **Why?** Affordable, great weather (Eternal Spring), strong internet, friendly locals.  \n- **Visa:** [Colombia Digital Nomad Visa](https://www.cancilleria.gov.co/)  \n- **Coworking spaces:** [Selina Cowork Medellín](https://www.selina.com/colombia/medellin/cowork/), [AtomHouse](https://atomhouse.co/)  \n- **Nomad resources:** [Medellin Guru](https://medellinguru.com/)  \n\n---\n\n### **4. Bali, Indonesia**  \n- **Why?** Tropical paradise, digital nomad hotspots like Canggu & Ubud, low living costs.  \n- **Visa:** [Indonesia Digital Nomad Visa (B211a)](https://www.imigrasi.go.id/en/)  \n- **Coworking spaces:** [Dojo Bali](https://dojobali.org/), [Tropical Nomad](https://www.tropicalnomad.co/)  \n- **Nomad resources:** [Nomad List - Bali](https://nomadlist.com/bali-indonesia)  \n\n---\n\n### **5. Mexico City, Mexico**  \n- **Why?** Thriving expat scene, huge coworking culture, vibrant nightlife & food.  \n- **Visa:** [Mexico Temporary Resident Visa](https://www.inm.gob.mx/)  \n- **Coworking spaces:** [WeWork Mexico City](https://www.wework.com/l/mexico-city--mexico), [Centraal](https://centraal.com/)  \n- **Nomad resources:** [Mexico City Relocation Guide](https://breathewithus.com/mexico-city-living-guide/)  \n\n---\n\n### **6. Budapest, Hungary**  \n- **Why?** Affordable EU living, great infrastructure, beautiful architecture.  \n- **Visa:** [Hungary White Card (Remote Work Visa)](https://enterhungary.com/)  \n- **Coworking spaces:** [KAPTÁR](https://kaptar.hu/), [K10 Coworking](https://k10.hu/)  \n- **Nomad resources:** [Budapest Nomad Guide](https://offbeatbudapest.com/)  \n\n---\n\n### **7. Tbilisi, Georgia**  \n- **Why?** Extremely cheap, no visa required for 1 year (for many nationalities).  \n- **Visa:** [Georgia's Remote Work Program](https://stopcov.ge/en/)  \n- **Coworking spaces:** [Impact Hub Tbilisi](https://tbilisi.impacthub.net/), [Workshop](https://workshop.com.ge/)  \n- **Nomad resources:** [Tbilisi Digital Nomad Guide](https://expathub.ge/)  \n\n---\n\n### **8. Barcelona, Spain**  \n- **Why?** High quality of life, beaches, strong digital nomad ecosystem.  \n- **Visa:** [Spain Digital Nomad Visa](https://www.exteriores.gob.es/)  \n- **Coworking spaces:** [Betahaus](https://www.betahaus.com/barcelona/), [Aticco](https://www.aticco.com/)  \n- **Nomad resources:** [Barcelona Digital Nomads](https://www.meetup.com/barcelonanomads/)  \n\n---\n\n### **Bonus Mentions:**  \n- **Tallinn, Estonia** ([Estonia Digital Nomad Visa](https://www.kmu.ee/en/))  \n- **Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam** ([Vietnam e-Visa](https://evisa.xuatnhapcanh.gov.vn/))  \n- **Berlin, Germany** ([Freelancer Visa](https://service.berlin.de/))  \n\nFor real-time reviews & rankings, check:  \n- **[Nomad List](https://nomadlist.com/)** (comparisons & cost breakdowns)  \n- **[SafetyWing Nomad Insurance](https://safetywing.com/)** (recommended for travelers)  \n\nWould you like recommendations based on specific priorities (cost, visa ease, internet speed, etc.)?",
